Dogecoin Core 1.16 fully syncs on main and test networks. 1,17 has changed how blocks are loaded (again), so it will take more time to verify the AuxPoW changes as we apply them, but that's on track for later this week.
Also, seriously, NEVER JUMP FOUR VERSIONS. So many painful lessons from that one. 1.16 has been so much easier so far.

Plan is to get 1.14 out (having branding issues that need nailing down), get most nodes updated to that, and we can then hopefully roll out 1.16. Trying not to jump 4 versions in a batch this time, it rather overcomplicates.
